---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Humanoids — Formic"
  description="Humanoid and bimanual mobile platforms for manufacturers: deployed, supported, and continuously upgraded under Formic Full Service. Fixed monthly price, no CapEx, no internal R&D required."
  ogTitle="Humanoids — Formic"
  ogDescription="Humanoid and bimanual platforms under Formic Full Service. Frontier capability, no internal R&D required."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/humanoids" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Humanoids
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Humanoids</div>
    <h1>Generalist robots,<br><em>as a service.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Humanoid and bimanual mobile platforms for manufacturers: deployed, supported, and continuously upgraded under Formic Full Service. Fixed monthly price, no CapEx, no internal R&amp;D required.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Humanoid-factory.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-cap">Bimanual platform · pilot cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why Now</div>
      <h2>General-purpose robotics is <em>finally shipping</em>.</h2>
      <p>For decades, general-task automation was the perpetual "five years away" of manufacturing. That changed. Bimanual mobile robots and humanoid platforms are no longer lab hardware — they are running production cycles in pilot programs at real manufacturing facilities today.</p>
      <p>Formic is the deployment partner for mid-market manufacturers who want frontier capability without becoming a robotics R&amp;D shop themselves.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Pilots designed and run by Formic engineers</li>
        <li>Same Full Service model — fixed monthly price, no CapEx, all support included</li>
        <li>Continuous OTA upgrades as capability matures</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Humanoid-factory.jpg" alt="Humanoid robot working on a factory floor" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Frontier · production trial</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-9787.jpg" alt="Bimanual mobile manipulator" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Mobile · bimanual</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Mobile Bimanual</div>
      <h2>Two arms, one base, <em>anywhere on the line</em>.</h2>
      <p>Bimanual mobile robots handle multi-step manipulation tasks — bin picking, machine tending, kitting, and assist work — and relocate between cells without a fixed footprint. Most useful where the work is too varied for fixed automation but too repetitive for skilled labor.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Bimanual manipulation for two-handed tasks</li>
        <li>SLAM-based navigation, no fixed track required</li>
        <li>Task-level instruction via demonstration, not g-code — operators show the robot, not program it</li>
        <li>Designed for shared-space operation alongside human teams</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Humanoid Pilots</div>
      <h2>Pilot today. <em>Scale tomorrow.</em></h2>
      <p>We're running humanoid pilots with select customers in 2026 and 2027. Pilots are scoped narrowly — one task, one cell, one shift — and expanded only when the platform proves out economics.</p>
      <p>Pilots are priced under the same Full Service monthly model: no capital at risk if the platform doesn't prove out.</p>
      <a href="/talk-with-an-expert" class="larr">Discuss a pilot →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Humanoid-factory.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Humanoid · pilot trial</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:flex-start">What's Included</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(32px,4.4vw,64px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1.04;color:var(--white);margin:10px 0 14px">One monthly fee. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Everything included.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Pilot scoping and cell design</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Platform deployment and commissioning</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Task programming and demonstration-based training</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>24/7 monitoring and support</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>OTA capability upgrades</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>All maintenance and parts</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Direct vendor roadmap access</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Performance SLAs</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Frontier capability,<br><em>without the R&amp;D shop.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="/talk-with-an-expert" class="btn-ctadark">Talk with an Expert</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
